        "sear_text": "Back Cover: The Legend of the Great Stupa: Prosperous by virtue of diligent work, the poultrywoman Shamvara and her four sons aspire to build a Great Stupa- a reliquary for the remains of the Buddhas and a place of adoration for innumerable beings. Great were the benefits conveyed through this meritorious action. When the sons were later renuited to transmit the Dharma in Tibet, Padmasambhava related the Stupa's creation and described how, after its destruction in the dark ages to come, it would be rebuild, restoring harmony and balance to the world. This tale of slefless devotion, told to Trisong Detsen, King of Tibet, bt the Great Guru Padmasambhava illustrates the power of faith that presits through cosmic cycles of growth and decay. It conveys the importance of symbols that can focus resolve, enrich it with knowledge, and disseminate the blessings of wisdom and compassion to all beings.",
