        "sear_text": "Back cover : A pond of Lotuses.\nOut of compassion for all gods and humans, I\nsurveyed the world with the eye of a Buddha to\nsee the minds of all beings. Just as in a pond of\nblue or red or white lotuses, some lotuses that\nare born in the water and grow in the water,\nremain in the water without rising out of it;\nsome other lotuses that are born in the water\nand grow in the water, rest on the water's\nsurface; and some other lotuses that are born in\nthe water and grow in the water, rise out of the\nwater and stand above, unwetted by the water.\nSo too, I saw beings with few defilements in\ntheir hearts and beings with many defilements\nin their hearts; with developed skills and\nundeveloped skills; with good qualities and\nwith bad qualities; easy to teach the reality of\nlife and difficult to teach the reality of life; and\nsome who live with fear of unwholesome\nactions and the next life, and some who live\nwithout fear of unwholesome actions and the\nnext life.\nThen I replied to the Brahmä Sahampati in\nstanzas:\n\"Aparutà tesam amatassa duârà\nye sotavanto pamuncantu saddham\"\nNow I open the golden door of Nibbana, the\nultimate deliverance to the wise. Let those who\nwish to listen to Noble Dhamma come with\npleasant minds.\nGautama Supreme Buddha,\nAriyapariyesanà Sutta - MN 26",
